org.spongepowered.api.service.user

Interface UserStorageService


  • public interface UserStorageService
    Stores the persistent User data of a Player.

      • get

        Optional<User> get(String lastKnownName)
        Gets the data of a User by their last known user name (case-insensitive).

        To get the current name of a player, use the GameProfileManager service.

        Parameters:
        lastKnownName - The user name
        Returns:
        User or Optional.empty() if not found

        Returns:
        User or Optional.empty() if not found

      • getOrCreate

        User getOrCreate(GameProfile profile)
        Gets or creates a persistent User associated with the given GameProfile.

        To obtain a GameProfile, use the GameProfileManager.

        Parameters:
        profile - The profile
        Returns:
        The user object

      • getAll

        Collection<GameProfile> getAll()
        Gets the collection of all GameProfiles with stored User data.

        Note that this method is resource-intensive depending on the amount of stored data.

        Use get(GameProfile) to get the User data corresponding to a GameProfile.

        Returns:
        A Collection of GameProfiles

      • delete

        boolean delete(GameProfile profile)
        Deletes the data associated with a User.

        This may not work if the user is logged in.

        Parameters:
        profile - The profile of the user to delete
        Returns:
        true if the deletion was successful

      • delete

        boolean delete(User user)
        Deletes the data associated with a User.

        This may not work if the user is logged in.

        Parameters:
        user - The user to delete
        Returns:
        true if the deletion was successful

      • match

        Collection<GameProfile> match(String lastKnownName)
        Returns a collection of matching GameProfiles with stored User data whose last known user names start with the given string (case-insensitive).

        Use get(GameProfile) to get the User data corresponding to a GameProfile.

        Parameters:
        lastKnownName - The user name
        Returns:
        The result of the request
